  "text": "A high variability in Th2 cell cytokine expression was detected in the group of CRSwNP specimens: IL-4 expressing T cells represented 1 to 15% of the CD4+ T cells. Asthmatic patients had the highest number of Th2 cells, this observation also being linked to the expression of SE-IgE antibodies, confirming our earlier analysis based on protein data; those data also showed a great variety of cytokine expression in CRSwNP samples, and a highly increased risk of being asthmatic with the expression of IL-5 and SE-IgE [CITATION_1] .",
